@startuml Sequence_Diagram_2_Dashboard

title Sequence Diagram 2: View Dashboard (Parallel Data Loading)

actor "Cashier" as Cashier
participant "MainWindow" as MainWindow
participant "DashboardView\n(FXML)" as UI
participant "DashboardController" as Controller
participant "ChickenDAO" as ChickenDAO
participant "EggProductionDAO" as EggDAO
participant "MortalityDAO" as MortalityDAO
participant "DateUtil" as DateUtil
participant "DatabaseConnection" as DB

== Dashboard Initialization ==

Cashier -> MainWindow: After successful login
MainWindow -> UI: Load DashboardView.fxml
UI -> Controller: initialize()
activate Controller

note right of Controller
    <b>Dashboard loads 4 metrics:</b>
    1. Total chickens (all houses)
    2. Eggs produced today
    3. Deaths today (for alerts)
    4. 7-day egg production chart
    
    <b>Loading Strategy:</b>
    All metrics loaded in parallel
    for better performance
end note

== Load Total Chickens ==

par Load Total Chickens Count
    Controller -> ChickenDAO: getAllChickens()
    activate ChickenDAO
    
    ChickenDAO -> DB: getConnection()
    activate DB
    DB --> ChickenDAO: Connection
    deactivate DB
    
    ChickenDAO -> DB: executeQuery(\n"SELECT * FROM chickens")
    activate DB
    DB --> ChickenDAO: List<Chicken> (ResultSet)
    deactivate DB
    
    ChickenDAO -> ChickenDAO: Map ResultSet to List<Chicken>
    
    loop For each chicken batch
        ChickenDAO -> ChickenDAO: totalCount += batch.getQuantity()
    end
    
    ChickenDAO --> Controller: totalCount (17,209 chickens)
    deactivate ChickenDAO
    
    Controller -> UI: Update totalChickensLabel
    UI -> UI: Display "17,209"

== Load Today's Egg Production ==

else Load Eggs Produced Today
    Controller -> EggDAO: getTodayProduction()
    activate EggDAO
    
    EggDAO -> DB: getConnection()
    activate DB
    DB --> EggDAO: Connection
    deactivate DB
    
    EggDAO -> DateUtil: getCurrentDate()
    activate DateUtil
    DateUtil --> EggDAO: LocalDate.now()
    deactivate DateUtil
    
    EggDAO -> DB: executeQuery(\n"SELECT SUM(eggsCollected)\nFROM egg_production\nWHERE collectionDate = ?")
    activate DB
    DB --> EggDAO: totalEggs (4,200)
    deactivate DB
    
    EggDAO --> Controller: 4,200 eggs
    deactivate EggDAO
    
    Controller -> UI: Update eggsProducedTodayLabel
    UI -> UI: Display "4,200"

== Load Active Alerts ==

else Load Active Alerts
    Controller -> MortalityDAO: getDeathsToday()
    activate MortalityDAO
    
    MortalityDAO -> DB: getConnection()
    activate DB
    DB --> MortalityDAO: Connection
    deactivate DB
    
    MortalityDAO -> DateUtil: getCurrentDate()
    activate DateUtil
    DateUtil --> MortalityDAO: LocalDate.now()
    deactivate DateUtil
    
    MortalityDAO -> DB: executeQuery(\n"SELECT SUM(count)\nFROM mortality\nWHERE deathDate = ?")
    activate DB
    DB --> MortalityDAO: deathCount (11)
    deactivate DB
    
    MortalityDAO --> Controller: 11 deaths
    deactivate MortalityDAO
    
    Controller -> Controller: calculateAlerts()
    note right
        <b>Alert Logic:</b>
        • Mortality rate > 5%: HIGH alert
        • Low feed stock: MEDIUM alert
        • Broken equipment: LOW alert
        
        Total alerts = 2
    end note
    
    Controller -> UI: Update activeAlertsLabel
    UI -> UI: Display "2 Active Alerts"

== Load 7-Day Production Chart ==

else Load 7-Day Production Chart
    Controller -> DateUtil: getLast7Days()
    activate DateUtil
    DateUtil --> Controller: LocalDate[] (7 dates)
    deactivate DateUtil
    
    Controller -> EggDAO: getLast7DaysProduction()
    activate EggDAO
    
    EggDAO -> DB: getConnection()
    activate DB
    DB --> EggDAO: Connection
    deactivate DB
    
    EggDAO -> DB: executeQuery(\n"SELECT collectionDate, SUM(eggsCollected)\nFROM egg_production\nWHERE collectionDate >= ?\nGROUP BY collectionDate")
    activate DB
    DB --> EggDAO: List<EggProduction> (7 days)
    deactivate DB
    
    EggDAO --> Controller: production data
    deactivate EggDAO
    
    Controller -> Controller: prepareChartData()
    note right
        Format data for BarChart:
        X-axis: Dates (dd/MM format)
        Y-axis: Egg count
        
        Data points:
        08/12: 4,100
        09/12: 4,200
        10/12: 3,950
        ...
    end note
    
    Controller -> UI: Update productionChart
    UI -> UI: Render 7-day bar chart
    
end

deactivate Controller

UI -> Cashier: Display complete dashboard\nwith all 4 metrics

note bottom of Admin
    <b>Dashboard Display:</b>
    
    ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
    │  📊 Total Chickens: 17,209      │
    │  🥚 Eggs Today: 4,200           │
    │  ⚠️  Active Alerts: 2            │
    │                                 │
    │  📈 7-Day Egg Production        │
    │  [Bar Chart showing trend]      │
    └─────────────────────────────────┘
end note

@enduml
